                            <comment id="12993640" author="mgrigorov" created="Fri, 11 Feb 2011 19:00:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3405&quot; title=&quot;POST fails if request.getParameter called by ServletFilter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-3405&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-3405&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994340" author="wolfftw" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 15:39:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, but this is not a duplicate of 3405.  If user retrieves HttpServletRequest, e.g. within a page constructor, and attempts to read parameters, because of how parameters are read by ServletWebRequest (via reader), an IllegalStateException will be thrown by HttpServletRequest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994341" author="mgrigorov" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 15:43:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please create a quickstart against 1.5-SNAPSHOT that reproduces the problem and attach it to this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994558" author="wolfftw" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 23:29:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s a quickstart?  If you can send me a link to instructions I will try and carve out some time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
